==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moonstone
<hw>Moon"stone`</hw> <pr>(m⟦oomac⟧n"st⟦omac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A nearly pellucid variety of feldspar, showing
pearly or opaline reflections from within. It is used as a gem. The best
specimens come from Ceylon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moonstricken</ent>⟦br⟧
